---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/content-pages.css";
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy policy | mozgrozmowy.pl"
	description="Privacy and data processing information for mozgrozmowy.pl."
	lang="en"
	pathname="/en/privacy-policy/"
	alternatePath="/privacy-policy/"
>
	<main class="page-shell">
		<section class="page-intro page-intro--alt">
			<p class="page-kicker">Privacy</p>
			<h1>Privacy policy</h1>
			<p>
				This website is intentionally simple: it publishes content and does not use
				tracking tools for user profiling.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="about-card surface-card">
			<h2>1. Website controller</h2>
			<p>
				The controller of this website is the author and owner of the
				mozgrozmowy.pl project.
			</p>

			<h2>2. What data may be processed</h2>
			<p>
				The website does not use user accounts, registration forms, marketing
				forms, or tools designed to track users across pages or services.
			</p>
			<p>
				From a technical perspective, the hosting provider and server may process
				basic data necessary to display the website and maintain security, such as
				IP address, request date, browser type, or server logs.
			</p>

			<h2>3. Cookies</h2>
			<p>
				At the time of publication, the website does not use non-essential cookies
				for analytics, advertising, or marketing purposes.
			</p>
			<p>
				If such features are added in the future, this privacy policy will be
				updated accordingly.
			</p>

			<h2>4. Contact</h2>
			<p>
				If you contact me by email, I process the data included in your message
				only for the purpose of replying and continuing communication about that
				matter.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Your rights</h2>
			<p>
				You have the right to information about data processing, access to your
				data, rectification, erasure, or restriction of processing — to the extent
				provided by applicable law.
			</p>

			<h2>6. Changes</h2>
			<p>
				This policy may be updated in the future if the technical operation of the
				website changes.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
